head.note:
In English, Spanish, Portuguese, and French;
                                    English text, only, printed. Ratification advised by the Senate,
                                    with a reservation, June 15 (legislative day of June 6), 1934;
                                    ratified by the President, with said reservation, June 29, 1934;
                                    ratification of the United States deposited with the Pan
                                    American Union, July 13, 1934; proclaimed by the President,
                                    January 18, 1935.
